population just takes off.

00:14:30.340 --> 00:14:34.129
You've heard of exponential
population growth,

00:14:34.129 --> 00:14:36.759
and you may or may not know
what that means,

00:14:36.759 --> 00:14:39.847
but what it precisely means is
there's a certain rate of

00:14:39.847 --> 00:14:42.166
growth,
a certain percent per year,

00:14:42.166 --> 00:14:45.940
and each year the population
grows by that same percent,

00:14:45.940 --> 00:14:50.144
1% a year, 2% a year,
3% a year, but the percentage

00:14:50.144 --> 00:14:51.908
growth is constant.
 

00:14:51.908 --> 00:14:55.384
The numbers of people added
every year grows because the

00:14:55.384 --> 00:14:59.114
base grows, but the percentage
added every year is constant,

00:14:59.114 --> 00:15:01.009
that's exponential growth.
 

00:15:01.009 --> 00:15:04.740
In fact, during this period,
in fact during most of this

00:15:04.740 --> 00:15:08.808
period, the percentage rate of
growth has been increasing.

00:15:08.808 --> 00:15:16.952
It increased from somewhere out
here of .001% to then 0.01,0.1

00:15:16.952 --> 00:15:22.158
and in this period it went up to
2%,

00:15:22.158 --> 00:15:26.553
even 3% globally,
the whole world population

00:15:26.553 --> 00:15:30.950
growth rate in this incredible
expansion.

00:15:30.950 --> 00:15:34.110
As you can sort of see again,
in this somewhat schematized

00:15:34.110 --> 00:15:36.653
graph,
that the incredible rate of

00:15:36.653 --> 00:15:41.193
